     * [https://github.com/Pragmatists/eventsourcing-java-example]Event
       Sourcing Example (Java) - A simplified (in memory) example of Event
       Sourcing and CQRS implementation for Java code (modeled for banking
       domain use cases).
     * [https://github.com/andreschaffer/event-sourcing-cqrs-examples]Even
       t Sourcing and CQRS Examples - A pragmatic application of Event
       Sourcing and CQRS in Java with good references for common related
       problems, e.g. event ordering and idempotency.
     * [https://github.com/franzose/symfony-ddd-wishlist]DDD Wish List - A
       sample application in PHP built with Symfony 3 and Vue.js.
     * [https://github.com/pilloPl/event-source-cqrs-sample]Event Sourcing
       and CQRS Sample - Sample event sourced application with Command
       Query Responsibility Segregation
     * [https://github.com/thenativeweb/wolkenkit-todomvc]wolkenkit-todomv
       c - TodoMVC built with DDD, CQRS and event-sourcing
     * [https://github.com/eulerfx/DDDInventoryItemFSharp]DDDInventoryItem
       FSharp - An idiomatic F# implementation of Domain-Driven Design

Libraries and Frameworks

     * [https://geteventstore.com/]Event Store - The open-source,
       functional database with Complex Event Processing in JavaScript.
     * [http://www.axonframework.org/]Axon Framework - The axon framework
       is focused on making life easier for developers that want to create
       a java application based on the CQRS principles.
     * [https://github.com/QuickenLoans/MessageRouter]MessageRouter -
       Described in this video: [https://vimeo.com/171178586]The Beating
       Heart of CQRS, or Actor-Based Message Routing on the CLR by
       Paulmichael Blasucci at the New York F# .NET User Group.
     * [https://github.com/NEventStore/NEventStore]NEventStore - A
       persistence library used to abstract different storage
       implementations when using event sourcing as storage mechanism.
     * [https://github.com/yreynhout/Projac]Projac - Projac is a set of
       projection libraries that allow you to write projections targetting
       various backing stores.
     * [https://github.com/yevhen/Streamstone]Streamstone - Event Store
       for Azure Table Storage.
     * [https://github.com/tpierrain/Value]Value - Help you to easily
       implement Value Types in your C# projects without making errors nor
       polluting your domain logic with boiler-plate code.
     * [https://github.com/d60/Cirqus]Cirqus - d60 event sourcing + CQRS
       framework.
     * [https://github.com/jonsequitur/Its.Cqrs]Its.Cqrs - A set of
       libraries for CQRS and Event Sourcing, with a Domain-Driven Design
       flavor.
     * [https://github.com/yreynhout/aggregateSource]AggregateSource -
       Lightweight infrastructure for doing eventsourcing using
       aggregates.
     * [https://github.com/yreynhout/JESA]JESA - Event sourced aggregates
       for Java.
     * [https://github.com/eventflow/EventFlow]EventFlow - Async/await
       first CQRS+ES and DDD framework for .NET
       [http://geteventflow.net/]http://geteventflow.net/.
     * [http://cqrs.js.org/]cqrs.js - CQRS implementations in node.js.
       Includes [https://github.com/adrai/node-eventstore]node-eventstore,
       [https://github.com/adrai/node-cqrs-domain]node-cqrs-domain,
       [https://github.com/adrai/node-cqrs-eventdenormalizer]node-eventden
       ormalizer, [https://github.com/adrai/node-cqrs-saga]node-cqrs-saga.
     * [https://eventsourcing.com/]Eventsourcing - Business event capture
       and querying framework.
     * [https://github.com/MerrionComputing/CQRSAzure]CQRS on Azure CQRS
       on Windows Azure.
     * [http://seedstack.org/docs/business/]SeedStack's Business Framework
       - A set of building blocks that enable you to code business logic
       according to the Domain-Driven Design (DDD) approach.
     * [https://github.com/damianh/SqlStreamStore]SqlStreamStore - .NET
       Stream Store library targeting SQL based implementations.
     * [https://github.com/damianh/Cedar.CommandHandling]Cedar.CommandHand
       ling - Middleware to handling commands over HTTP; typically used in
       CQRS applications.
     * [https://github.com/Particular/NServiceBus]NServiceBus - Service
       bus for .NET.
     * [https://github.com/MassTransit/MassTransit]MassTransit -
       Distributed Application Framework for .NET.
     * [http://getakka.net/]Akka.NET - Akka.NET is a toolkit and runtime
       for building highly concurrent, distributed, and fault tolerant
       event-driven applications on .NET & Mono.
     * [http://aspnetboilerplate.com/]ASP.NET Boilerplate - ASP.NET MVC,
       Web API and ASP.NET Core based application framework to create
       NLayered, Domain Driven Designed web Applications implementing best
       practices.
     * [https://github.com/volak/Aggregates.NET]Aggregates.NET - .NET
       event sourced domain driven design model via NServicebus and
       GetEventStore.
     * [https://github.com/mission202/Stringly.Typed]Stringly.Typed -
       Making it easier to convert strings to/from .NET types.
     * [https://github.com/slashdotdash/commanded]Commanded - Command
       handling middleware for CQRS/ES applications, Pure Functional Data
       Structures for Aggregates and Process Managers, Point-to-Point
       message routing, and much more in Elixir (Erlang VM) - All in Actor
       concurrency model.
     * [https://github.com/pawelkaczor/akka-ddd]akka-ddd - Reusable
       artifacts for building applications on top of the Akka platform
       following CQRS/DDDD-based approach.
     * [https://github.com/slashdotdash/eventstore]eventstore - CQRS event
       store using PostgreSQL for persistence.
     * [https://github.com/talyssonoc/node-api-boilerplate]Node API
       Boilerplate - NodeJS web API boilerplate for DDD and Clean
       Architecture applications.
     * [https://www.wolkenkit.io/]wolkenkit - A CQRS, DDD, and
       event-sourcing framework for JavaScript and Node.js.
     * [https://github.com/broadway/broadway]Broadway - Broadway is a
       (PHP) project providing infrastructure and testing helpers for
       creating CQRS and event sourced applications.
     * [https://github.com/ElderJames/shriek-fx]shriek-fx - An
       simple,elegant and useful Domain-Driven Design and CQRS framework
       developed using .NET Core 2.0.
     * [https://railseventstore.org/]Rails Event Store - Rails Event Store
       (RES) is a library for publishing, consuming, storing and
       retrieving events. It's your best companion for going with an
       event-driven architecture for your Rails application.
     * [https://github.com/otobus/event_bus]Event Bus - Traceable,
       extendable and minimalist event bus implementation for Elixir with
       built-in event store and event watcher based on ETS.
     * [https://www.lagomframework.com/]Lagom - The Lagom Framework is a
       microservices framework for the Java Virtual Machine, with APIs for
       the Java and Scala languages. It includes an Event Sourcing/CQRS
       based persistence module.
     * [https://github.com/jeyjeyemem/Xer.Cqrs]Xer.Cqrs - A simple library
       for creating applications based on the CQRS pattern with support
       for attribute routing and hosted handlers. Developed in C#
       targeting .NET Standard 1.0.

